parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash, as the airbags may not deploy to cushion the impact.

dashboard bulging near the airbag section
airbags failing to deploy in a crash
injuries or fatalities due to lack of airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of dashboard and interior components can lead to a loss of structural integrity, causing injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash.
symptoms: side view mirrors shaking or breaking off
door handles turning brittle and breaking off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can lead to loss of control of the vehicle, resulting in accidents and injuries.

loss of control of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fraudulent sales practices can lead to buyers being unaware of critical safety issues, such as disabled airbag systems, which can put them at risk of injury or fatality.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EGR valve can cause the check engine light to come on, leading to failed smog tests and potentially causing engine performance issues.
The failure of the water pump can cause the serpentine belt to break, leading to loss of power steering and braking, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Loud banging or clanging noise from the engine compartment

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the engine can cause the vehicle to lose power and potentially lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Warped brake rotors can cause the steering wheel to vibrate when the brakes are applied, leading to reduced vehicle control and increased stopping distances, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel vibrates when the brakes are applied
the brake pedal moves toward the floor when at a complete stop
